> Step aside, side salad—this hearty kale version is the stuff of lunch dreams. 
> We mix the tenderized greens with cooked chicken, apple slices, cabbage, 
> and carrot, then we toss it with a creamy, tangy honey Dijon dressing and 
> sprinkle it with chili flakes for a warming kick. This is a hearty-yet-light-feeling 
> lunch idea you're going to want to make even when it's not harvest season.

Wash and dry produce. Pat @Fully Cooked Chicken Breasts{9%ounce} dry with 
#paper towels{}; dice into ½-inch pieces. Halve, core, and dice 
@Granny Smith Apple{1}(diced).

Place @Kale{4%ounce} in a #large bowl{} and drizzle with @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon}. 
Using your hands, massage kale until leaves are tender, ~{1-2%minutes}. 
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add chicken, @Coleslaw Mix{4%ounce}, apple, 2⁄3 of the @Honey Dijon Dressing{3%ounce}, 
a pinch of salt, and pepper to bowl; toss to combine.

Divide salad between #bowls{}. Drizzle with remaining dressing and sprinkle with 
as many @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Season with salt and pepper and serve.